There are four ways to trigger the automation scripts:
1.By using the pom.xml file
2.By using the CLI
3.By using the run.bat file
4.By using the Jenkins

1. By using the pom.xml file(maven-surefire-plugin and maven-compiler-plugin required)
Steps:
      1.Right click on the project-->Run As-->Maven clean //To clean the project
      2.Right click on the project-->Run As-->Maven test  //To run the tests
      OR
      1.Right click on the project-->Run As-->Maven clean //To clean the project
      2.Right click on the project-->Run As-->Maven install //To clean the project
      OR
      1.Right click on the project-->Run As-->Maven Build-->clean install-->Apply-->Run
      
2. By using the CLI
Steps: 
      1. Download the maven from official website https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi?. click on binary zip archieve
      2. Extract the folder and paste in the c: drive 
      3. Set the environment variable
      
